snippet: The Inland Empire region, which includes San Bernardino and Riverside Counties, is experiencing a boom in development of warehouses and logistics centers.
abstract: California's Inland Empire, once cautionary tale of perils of overdevelopment during financial crisis, is experiencing resurgence; region, which encompasses San Bernardino and Riverside Counties, had most industrial space under construction nationwide in second quarter of 2015, by margin of some 10 million square feet; observers say they are unconcerned about second bubble, given warehousing needs of nearby Los Angeles and Long Beach.
lead_paragraph: The Inland Empire region, which includes San Bernardino and Riverside Counties, is experiencing a boom in development of warehouses and logistics centers.

headline.main: In California’s Inland Empire, an Economic Recovery Brimming With Industrial Complexes
headline.print_headline: Bringing the Industry Back to an Empire
